import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    sns.set_style("darkgrid")
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='price', data=data, color='blue')
    chart.axhline(y=data['price'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    chart.axhline(y=data['price'].min(), color='green', linestyle='--', label='Min')
    chart.axhline(y=data['price'].max(), color='orange', linestyle='--', label='Max')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['price'] = pd.to_numeric(data['price'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['price'])]
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='price', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['price'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of daily closing prices for the S&P 500 index?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Price')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    data['month_year'] = data['date'].dt.strftime('%Y-%m')
    avg_price = data.groupby(['year', 'month_year'])['price'].mean().reset_index()
    plt.figure(figsize=(16, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='month_year', y='price', data=avg_price, color='blue')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('Month-Year')
    plt.ylabel('Average Daily Closing Price')
    plt.axhline(y=avg_price['price'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average Closing Price')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    sns.set(style="darkgrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 8))
    ax = sns.scatterplot(x="date", y="price", data=data, color='blue', label='S&P 500 Index')
    ax.set_ylabel('S&P 500 Index Price')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax2 = ax.twinx()
    ax2 = sns.lineplot(x="date", y="gdp", data=data, color='red', label='GDP')
    ax2.set_ylabel('GDP')
    ax3 = ax.twinx()
    ax3 = sns.lineplot(x="date", y="unemployment_rate", data=data, color='green', label='Unemployment Rate')
    ax3.set_ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    ax3.spines["right"].set_position(("axes", 1.1))
    ax3.set_ylim(0, 12)
    ax3.set_xlim(data['date'].min(), data['date'].max())
    plt.title('What is the correlation between the S&P 500 index and other economic indicators such as GDP or unemployment rate?', wrap=True)
    ax.legend(loc='upper left')
    ax2.legend(loc='upper right')
    ax3.legend(loc='lower left')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    sns.set_style("darkgrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 8))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['price'].pct_change(), color='blue')
    ax.axhline(y=data['price'].pct_change().mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    ax.axhline(y=data['price'].pct_change().std(), color='green', linestyle='--', label='Standard Deviation')
    ax.legend(loc='upper left')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Daily Percentage Change')
    plt.title('What is the volatility of the S&P 500 index over the given time period?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
